We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

Experience the World Through Dance at nATFEST 2025!

Join us for nATFEST 2025, an extraordinary celebration of global movement and cultural exchange, proudly presented by nATANDA Dance Theatre of Sri Lanka. This is not just a festival ‚Äî it‚Äôs a living, breathing conversation between continents, rhythms, and souls.

From the elegant studios of Switzerland, the rich traditions of India, the avant-garde stages of Russia, the refined creativity of Austria, the powerful expressions from the UK, the bold innovation of Hong Kong, and the vibrant heart of Sri Lanka ‚Äî artists and audiences will come together in Colombo to witness dance that transcends borders.

This is your invitation to be part of a festival where tradition meets transformation, and where every performance is a window into another world. nATFEST 2025 is not to be missed ‚Äî come and see the world move!

**Actors wanted for Dick Whittington, Valley Theatre‚Äôs annual seasonal panto.**

**Audition date and time;**** 7.15pm, Monday 13****th**** October 2025, at Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA**

**Performance dates:**** Sat  17****th**** Jan 2026(afternoon and eve) and Sun  18****th**** Jan 2026 (afternoon only);**

**Rehearsal days;**** Monday 7pm whole cast usually; Thursday eve selected scenes.**

Valley Theatre‚Äôs traditional panto has become legendary in the area. As a community theatre we pride ourselves on keeping the prices family friendly without compromising on the quality. We like to offer a  traditional storyline with well-loved panto routines, popular music, up-to-date and local references, strong on humour.

This is a great opportunity for actors wanting to gain unbeatable stage experience  with a friendly and supportive production team.

Wide range of parts available for the experienced and beginner alike. No prep needed for the audition.

Please note: this is non-paying.

More details [info@valleytheatre.co.uk](mailto:info@valleytheatre.co.uk)

items.text:
‚Ä¢CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM 
Project Title: Before We Break
Production Type: Independent Feature Film
Shoot Dates: October 10th - 12th.
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $500/day (2 days) + Reel + IMDb Credit

SYNOPSIS:
A week before their high school‚Äôs final closure, five former classmates reunite to bury a time capsule they created years ago. What begins as a nostalgic farewell quickly spirals into a raw confrontation of the truths, betrayals, and dreams that shaped their youth and the adulthood that awaits.
NOW CASTING ‚Äì LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES:

 LEAD ROLES:

Malik (Male, 18‚Äì23)
Ambitious, witty, and fiercely protective. A natural leader haunted by a decision he made senior year that fractured the group.

Zoey (Female, 18‚Äì24)
Intelligent and emotionally layered. She‚Äôs the planner of the reunion, but secretly fears what might resurface. Carries herself with quiet authority.

Jessie (Female, 19‚Äì25)
Charming and impulsive with a magnetic presence. Struggles with stability and hides vulnerability behind a fearless exterior.

SUPPORTING ROLES:

Cam (Female, 18‚Äì23)
Reserved, observant, and deeply reflective. Once the outsider of the group, she now holds crucial pieces of the past they all want to forget.

Ms. Clarke (Female, 30s‚Äì40s)
A former teacher turned school counselor. Warm, insightful, and a mentor to many, but carries her own regrets about the group‚Äôs final year.

TO SUBMIT:
Email your headshot, resume, and city of residence to:
newdawnfilming@gmail.com 

Subject line: ‚Äú[Your Name] ‚Äì Role Submission for Before We Break‚Äù

items.text:
CASTING CALL 

Self Tapes Wanted for University of Colorado Denver Senior Thesis Project

In-Person Callbacks in early October

TITLE: *Action! 1987*

PROJECT TYPE: Short Film (Student, Non-Union)

LOCATION: Denver Metro Area

TIMEFRAME: 2 Days of Shooting in late October 

SYNOPSIS: In 1987, a young woman, Luda, leaves a movie theatre with her cinephile boyfriend Julian. They argue about the morality of the action heroes they see on screen. Luda says the so-called ‚Äúgood guys‚Äù are always doing bad things. Julian thinks it‚Äôs more complicated than that.

The next day at work while helping with a children‚Äôs beauty pageant, Luda finds that right and wrong aren‚Äôt always so black and white when the parents of a young girl, Angie, leaves her alone in front of Luda. That night Luda and Julian walk into the movie theatre and she is shocked to see herself up on the silver screen.

COMPENSATION (Non-Union) : Reel, Food, Gas, Undying Appreciation

ROLE: 

Dad (Male, Late 30‚Äôs - Late 40‚Äôs): An stern and demanding pageant Dad with a wandering eye.

Please send your headshot/resume/other materials to [MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU](mailto:MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU) to receive sides and further instructions for submitting a self-tape. Thank you!

items.text:
Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.
https://www.annemusisi.com

Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.

**Autumn greetings to all our actors from Estonia and beyond!** üçÇüçÅ

All-level Meisner workshop taking place in Tallinn soon!

Join us, November 15‚Äì16th, for a two-day workshop with actor coach Dominic Kelly.

Whether you‚Äôre just starting out or looking to deepen your practice, this course offers a focused exploration of Sanford Meisner‚Äôs core exercises‚Äîhelping you access and express your most truthful impulses in response to your partner‚Äôs behavior.

You‚Äôll learn to:
 ‚ú® access your most truthful impulses
 ‚ú® connect deeply with your partner
 ‚ú® strengthen your instincts & emotional expression
 ‚ú® create freedom to be fully present, on stage and in life

This workshop is both a training ground and a safe space to challenge yourself, explore truth in performance, and deepen your connection to others and the imaginary world of a scene.

For our alumni, we have the option to work on a short, self-chosen scene on the second day (Let us know by email in advance if you would like to do this)

  üóì When: **15‚Äì16 November 2025 | 10:00‚Äì16:00**
  üìç Where: **Tallinn, Old Town**
  üë• For: Actors, performers, directors, writers, coaches‚Äîanyone curious about living & working more truthfully

Casting Call ‚ú®‚ú®‚ú®‚ú®

Hi! My name is Madeleine Bloore. I‚Äôm a Writer-Director currently developing my own short film. I‚Äôm fortunate to be working with an incredibly talented team of filmmakers who are just as passionate as I am about bringing this story to life.

‚ÄòThe Lines We Crossed‚Äô is a raw and tender story of found family, the messiness of healing, and the unexpected power of being seen. Three lives, stitched together by loneliness, come alive in the light of connection - and in that light, hope can take root where none was meant to grow.

We are now on the lookout for our secondary characters: The parents üëÄ

With Cody as his prodigy carrying the family‚Äôs reputation, life for Mr. Kane drifts by in a haze of beer cans and worn-out sofas. He‚Äôd be lying if he claimed to enjoy watching his son in the boxing ring as much as he enjoys the money each victory brings through the door. In Mr.
Kane‚Äôs eyes, life is beautifully easy - so long as Cody keeps winning.

‚Ä¢ Male
‚Ä¢ 40-65 years
‚Ä¢ White/Caucasian
‚Ä¢ London Accent

üìçLocation: London
üí∞ Payment: Unpaid
‚ú® Great opportunity for actors looking to gain experience, showreel material, and festival exposure.

ü´µ Are you our Mr. Kane? ü´µ

Auditions are open now üé¨
Contact IG: @lines_we_crossed_film
or Madeleine Bloore directly here on Facebook.

Director's Vision:
With the retro soul of ‚ÄòThe Breakfast Club‚Äô blended with the early warmth of ‚ÄòFriends‚Äô, this film reshapes nostalgia into a heartfelt tale of friendship, human connection, and the enduring promise of hope.

As the writer and director, my vision for this film is to transport audiences into the nostalgic energy of the 80s - a vibrant, colorful, and effortlessly cool era - while keeping it deeply relatable for today‚Äôs teenagers and young adults. At its heart, this story reflects the universal struggles of growing up: finding our place, defining who we are, and learning who we can trust.

I want this film to remind us that life is full of unexpected opportunities, and that we are not bound to what we start out with. The future belongs to us - we just have to be brave enough to reach for it.

We can‚Äôt wait to hear from you üòâ

Kickass Filmmakers! It‚Äôs go time! Registration is now officially open for the 6th Annual 72-Hour Kickass Film Fest!

Think you have what it takes to write, shoot, and edit a short film in just 72 hours? We‚Äôre challenging you to push your creativity to the limit. Every team will be assigned a random genre, plus a line of dialogue, prop, and character that must be in your 5-7 minute film.

You don‚Äôt have to live in Colorado to compete, but you‚Äôll need to follow our time zone.

And the best part? After the challenge, you‚Äôll get to celebrate your hard work at a red-carpet premiere and awards night with over 300 filmmakers and film lovers!

This is just the beginning. We have so many exciting announcements in store for Season 6. Are you up for the challenge? Can you make a film in 72 hours? Register today!  Link in bio!

**CASTING ROLES OF THE JOKER AND CATWOMAN FOR BATMAN FAN FILM ON YOUTUBE**

Hi my name is Lucas Woolrich. I'm working on a Batman fan film titled Batman Gotham City Sirens. The film will be uploaded onto Youtube. The story for the film would see Batman/Bruce Wayne facing off against Harley Quinn, Catwoman, Poison Ivy, Deathstroke, Black Mask and The Joker.

Here is the list of characters I am looking to cast for the film.

**CATWOMAN**

**THE JOKER **(to be played similar to 2008‚Äôs The Dark Knight‚Äôs version of The Joker)

Filming will be on for one day at the Rachel Almond Dance Academy in Manchester. Filming would last for four hours. Payment would be ¬£20 an hour. Applicants must be 18 years old and over. Also have great improvising skills. Applicants will have to provide their own costume for the role.

Please e-mail me at** superheroes4@outlook.com** if you're interested. Please include resume and headshot. I would appreciate it. Thanks.

topComments.text: I'd have been good as batman. But can definitely play joker!

items.text:
We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk
